UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1148
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION urging the creation of an interstate compact for
2 a competitive electric transmission market using competitive bidding.
3 WHEREAS, anticompetitive policies in some states constrain efforts to modernize
4 and expand energy transmission assets; and
5 WHEREAS, these policies have hindered infrastructure growth and increased
6 transmission costs to ratepayers because the noncompetitive nature of the permitting and
7 siting process of transmission projects does not incentivize the reduction of costs or
8 optimization of benefits; and
9 WHEREAS, some of the most popular, anticompetitive laws discriminate against
10 out-of-state businesses, which may violate the commerce clause of the United States
11 Constitution; and
12 WHEREAS, market-led consumer demand for better products and services has
13 precipitated an increased need for power generation in the United States; and
14 WHEREAS, to maintain a viable and growing economy, ensure a secure and
15 reliable power supply in the United States, and promote economic prosperity for the
16 citizens of the Commonwealth, the transmission capacity of the current utility
17 infrastructure must be modernized and expanded in a way that is responsive to the needs
18 and demands of both citizens and businesses;
19 NOW, THEREFORE,
20 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the General Assembly of the
21 Commonwealth of Kentucky, the Senate concurring therein:
22 Section 1. The General Assembly calls for the creation of an interstate compact
23 for the development of a competitive electric transmission market that would:
24 (1) Be in the best interests of the electric utility ratepayer and the
25 Commonwealth's economy;
26 (2) Deploy the requisite technologies to enhance and modernize the transmission
27 grid; and
Page 1 of 2
