UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1148
1 (3) Improve the electric transmission grid's capacity to transport electric energy
2 while preventing transmission bottlenecks and congestion.
3 Section 2. Any interstate compact for the development of a competitive electric
4 transmission market should:
5 (1) Use uniform rules, requirements, and procedures for the permitting and siting
6 of transmission lines, upgrading or reconductoring of the transmission infrastructure, and
7 deploying grid-enhancing technologies across states within a regional transmission
8 organization for all types of electric generating units, regardless of the fuel or electric
9 generating technology used;
10 (2) Allocate costs in an unbiased, holistic manner to all beneficiaries of the
11 competitive transmission market;
12 (3) Streamline all permits and regulatory reviews when deploying innovative
13 grid-enhancing technologies;
14 (4) Open the bidding process to interstate transmission projects;
15 (5) Eliminate redundancies or instances of double permitting for different
16 intragovernmental units in the transmission siting and permitting process;
17 (6) Develop and prioritize what would be known as co-location superhighways
18 for streamlined permitting and coordinated infrastructure development projects when
19 possible; and
20 (7) Apply the compact equally to all states upon each legislature's adoption of the
21 compact.
22 Section 3. The Clerk of the House of Representatives is directed to transmit a
23 copy of this Resolution to the Governor and the commissioners of the Public Service
24 Commission.
